ğŸ”¹ What is Graph Isomorphism?

Two graphs Gâ‚(Vâ‚, Eâ‚) and Gâ‚‚(Vâ‚‚, Eâ‚‚) are isomorphic if:

There exists a one-to-one and onto mapping

Between their vertex sets

That preserves adjacency

ğŸ“Œ In simple words:
Graphs are structurally identical, even if drawn differently.

